verbose_text: In general, we found that DFP exposure alone was mildly proinflammatory in the serum, increasing the levels of proinflammatory cytokines IL-6 and KC (XREF_FIG) and reducing the levels of the anti-inflammatory cytokines IL-4, IL-5, and IL-10 (XREF_FIG), and liver, markedly increasing IL-6, IL-1beta, LIF and OSM mRNA expression.
